##At the beginning of the outbreak, a mother and daughter died in Wuhan for 20 days

MICRO-SIGNAL YITIAOTV

Feature description, a short original video every day, every day to tell a moving story, every day selected human beauty, every day to live a better life with me.

On February 5th, a story about a girl in Wuhan,

More than 1.2 million were read on Wechat that day.

She survived this new form of pneumonia by isolating herself at home,

At the same time, there are many more people who are going through life and death.

Wei Wei and mom

After the story was published,

Another girl in the article, Wei Wei, contacted US backstage that day,

Willing to volunteer my mom's therapy sessions.

He was admitted to Wuchang Hospital on January 13 and discharged on February 1,

Wei Wei's family has been transferred to three departments,

After nearly 20 days of difficult treatment, he was released from the hospital.

Weiwei's circle of friends on the day his mother left the hospital

She said, I want to share the story of our mother and daughter,

To show more people the positive energy of overcoming illness,

Tell everyone to stick to it,

If you keep at it, you'll see hope!

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A picture of Auntie Cheng and the medical staff at Wuchang Hospital

My mother was a little sick at first, in early January, she felt a little cold and fever, she went to the hospital first, see a doctor injection. At the time, I joked to her, the news is all about new pneumonia, and if you get a cold or a fever, you'll be quarantined.

I am 90, my mother is 63 years, after her retirement, often in the Bayi Art Group to participate in some of the elderly performances, the body is also OK, no chronic diseases and so on.

In retrospect, my mother may have been exposed the first time she went to the hospital.

* On the 12th, he had a sudden fever, palpitation and chest tightness, and was admitted to Wuchang Hospital the next day

On January 12, he developed a sudden fever and was admitted to Wuchang Hospital the next day

After coming back from the hospital, my mother had already recovered from a cold. After two or three days, on or about January 12, she had a fever again. This time, she felt very flustered and tight in the chest. Her heart was very uncomfortable and she could not breathe. Because Wuchang Hospital was close to our home, she had a fever and the next day she was admitted to the Cardiovascular Department of Wuchang Hospital.

At that time, the cardiovascular diagnosis is suspected of fever caused by Myocarditis, also did ECG, but the cause has not been found. Mother in the hospital these few days have not holiday, I work every day, go to the hospital department to see her, with her to eat.

* Transferred from Cardio to aspiration on the 16th of July, and the doctor told me to pray

On January 16, transferred from cardio to aspiration, the doctor told me to pray

One day when we were at our busiest, I got a call from the cardiovascular doctor. She said my mother was not well and wanted me to come quickly. I was very nervous and asked for leave from work.

The doctor called me into her office and told me that my mother had been in hospital for three or four days, and had been taking Cephalosporin III, Levofloxacin, and some anti inflammatory drugs, but the fever had not abated and she had to be transferred to respiratory medicine.

The worst part was my mom's lungs. Two CTS changed a lot. When she first came in, there was nothing wrong with the CT scan of her lungs, which might have been slightly inflamed. When the doctor called me that day, I could clearly see that my mother's lungs were Scaly, with many white patches evenly distributed at the end of her lobules. In the case of so many anti-inflammatory and anti-viral drugs, in three days it became so severe.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo of Aunty Cheng (third right)

I remember the first thing the smoking physician said to me was: your mother is not well, and all you do is pray that your mother is not COVID-19. When I heard that, everything went black.

But I pulled myself together, and I tried everything to save my mom. There was no room on the smoking floor, it was full of people, the hallway was full of people, and we ended up on the digestive floor with extra beds.

Since I was on a different floor, I spent every day in the head and digestive section, lining up for medicine.

Shortly after my mother transferred to respiratory medicine, my father also began to have a fever, he and my mother's situation is more similar, but once in the hospital in a worse condition. The first two days, my dad was shooting from a bench in the suction aisle, and I was running food up and down the stairs. After two days or so his white blood cells had dropped to almost zero, and his vital signs were especially bad, so he went straight to the ICU.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A few days after she was admitted to the hospital, Auntie Zheng was in the cardiology ward

There were so many patients in the smoking department, all the aisles were full, and the patients who didn't have beds just sat in the hallways to get shots, and I was really scared, but I had no choice, and that's when I started to wear a mask and have awareness of protection. I spent about 16 hours a day in the hospital with my mom, and I went at 8:00 in the morning, and I didn't get home until 12:30. Every day after coming home, take off all clothes, disinfect from inside to outside, wash, then wash hair, take a bath. Probably washed up again at 1:00 or 2:00 a.m. , then went back to the hospital at 8:00 the next morning.

In those days, my mother's condition became worse day by day, and she couldn't eat anything. One striking feature of the disease is lack of appetite. She only drinks a little porridge and has a recurring fever every day. Once in the afternoon, then again in the middle of the night, for nearly 10 days.

At that time I was also very afraid, I asked all my friends, girlfriends, let them help me find a way. After all this time, people still get burnt to a crisp. If you can't cure it, do you want to transfer to a third-class hospital?

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Aunt Zheng's second CT report

The doctor knows about me, too. She Says Your Dad's in the ICU, your mom's in bed. You have to be strong. Every day when I saw the doctor, my tears kept falling. The head nurse and the doctor consoled me by saying, you can't cry. If you cry, it will be even worse if mom sees you. So every time I was a tear wipe, and then turn to use a smiling face to face mom, encourage her.

Smoking a head nurse in internal medicine, she saw my parents like this, think I am very poor, secretly into my pocket mask, also took a nurse's hat. She said you need to wear a hat. It's too dangerous here, and the spray on your hair is too dangerous. Also told me to go home every day must wash hands, contact with her mother, accompany her to the toilet or help her get water, must wash hands, but also the nurse station special disinfectant for me to use. I washed my hands like crazy. They were all over the place.

One day I found a very dangerous situation, she kept shaking during the day because of fever, hands and feet spasm, she said very cold, chills. He's been breathing oxygen, but he's feeling a little hard to breathe. I called the doctor, who gave my mother an antipyretic suppository and an intramuscular injection to force the fever down, but there was still no sign of improvement.

* On the 19th of July, I suddenly had a bloody bowel movement, and I felt like I was losing my mother

On January 19th, I suddenly had a bloody bowel movement, and I felt like I was losing my mother

On the night of January 19th, my mother suddenly had a bloody bowel movement. She herself was more optimistic, saying it was probably hemorrhoids. The head nurse gave me a sampler and told my mother to take a sample next time and send it to the lab. When I saw the cup, it collapsed. There was very little. It was all blood.

When my mother was in the hospital, I went online and looked up a lot of cases and other people's posts, almost all of them mentioned blood in the stool when the disease got worse.

A little after midnight that night, I took the Measuring Cup to another building for analysis. I think the wind was cold that night, and that was the longest walk I've ever taken. I was shaking all over, and I thought I was going to lose my mom, and my dad wasn't sure what was going on, and I could be infected... the hopelessness, the hopelessness of it all.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Dr. Jeong has extra beds in the digestive aisle

* He was transferred to the ICU ward of Wuchang Hospital for Immunoglobulin injection on 20 January

On January 20, he was transferred to the ICU ward of Wuchang Hospital, where he was injected with Immunoglobulin

On the second day after mom's blood in her stool, the hospital leaders were very concerned about our family's situation and told me not to lose heart, or to summon up courage, "The corridor bed environment is not very good, also can not have a good rest, we try to let her to the environment slightly better place treatment. " The hospital suggested that the mother transferred to the ICU ward.

Wuchang Hospital is not a third-class hospital, I also considered the transfer of the problem, first, because all the third-class hospitals in Wuhan were full at that time, it was difficult to find beds; Second, I looked up the information, there is no specific medicine for new pneumonia at present, you might as well be in a hospital. So he agreed to transfer her to the ICU.

As it turned out, I made the right choice. The doctors and nurses in every department of Wuchang Hospital we met were very good.

On January 10, the situation in Wuhan was already very serious, but nucleic acid testing methods have not been widely used. The way to confirm the diagnosis is to check whether the known virus is negative. My father, who tested negative for all known viruses, was quickly diagnosed with new pneumonia, so he was transferred directly from the Intensive Care Unit at Wuchang Hospital to Jinyintan Hospital in Wuhan, while my mother was not diagnosed until she was transferred to the ICU.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Keep the medicine you give your mother every day in the refrigerator

My mom has been in the ICU, getting a lot of shots every day, organ-protective drugs, nutrition shots, all kinds of anti-viral and anti-infective shots, including Immunoglobulin. Every day from 8:00 in the morning, until 5:00 in the morning to play.

The doctor said to me, this disease is no specific medicine, can only use globulin or hormone therapy, assist and strengthen your resistance, the final victory of the virus or on your own. Since January 16th, the doctor has asked me to buy Human Immunoglobulin, which is very expensive. My father and my mother basically drink six bottles a day. A person's daily cost is 3,000 or 4,000 yuan.

Mom still had a fever the first two days she was in the ICU. She sends me a message every morning that she had a little fever last night. I told her, it doesn't matter, keep it up! Keep it up and YOU'LL BE FINE!

I was a very light sleeper during that time, and whenever she sent me the first message at 6:00 or 6:00, I would hear it, and I would respond immediately, I was like, great! Keep it up. Come on!

Wei-wei gave her mother a pep talk

I have no way to visit her, can only give her every day to give her blood, encourage her. I said you have to have confidence, you can't give up, you can survive and get through it. This disease is relatively long for middle-aged and elderly people. It is all over 20 days. It has a process. You are only halfway through the race now, and there is still half way to go, just hang in there.

I just keep on brainwashing her every day, keep on output, don't let her have any slack.

But I endured a great deal of fear on my own, and it was really a force of will that held me together. Because I was afraid that I would be infected, if I was infected, who would give me Globulins, life-saving drugs, there would be no one to take care of my parents, our family would be finished, so I can not be infected.

* On the 25th of July, his temperature stabilized and he began to have an appetite

January 25th. Temperature's stable. Appetite's starting to show

After about five days of continuous Immunoglobulin, the mother's temperature gradually stabilized.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Aunty Zheng poses with medical staff before she is discharged from hospital

Because she had been in the hospital for so long, my mother hadn't been watching the news at that time. She didn't know that it was a terrible thing.

Until her temperature stabilizes. She started telling me that she was feeling a little hungry in the ICU, and I was happy to hear that, and that an appetite meant that she was starting to heal and get better.

I remember on January 26, I also specifically on-line orders, trying to find a way to send a lot of ICU to eat, a variety of fruits, snacks. I told my mother must eat full, do not guarantee nutrition, how can not eat full recovery? At that time I also wrote a very long note, especially afraid to take delivery boy to see the hospital list. I thought, if no one picks me up, I'm going to ride my bike and have to get to the hospital.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Remarks to rider

And then as mom got more and more stable, she started doing nucleic acid tests. Two consecutive negative nucleic acid tests, with a 24-hour interval, are required to meet discharge criteria. My mother's test results are a Yin, a Yang, may not be very stable, she was in the ICU after a period of time.

* On January 1, two tests were negative and the ICU was discharged, but no car was available

On February 1, two tests came back negative, and the ICU released him, but no car would pick him up

It wasn't until February 1st, when both nucleic acid tests were negative, that the ICU announced she was discharged.

The day my mother was released from the hospital, Wuhan had been closed for nine days. I was identified by the community as a close contact, travel is very restricted, asked 120, the community car, volunteer convoy also did not respond. At that time, a good friend of mine knew, she happened to be in the media, offered to go to the hospital to pick up my mother, but also helped me record the mother discharged from the hospital this moment.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Press interview on discharge

I haven't seen my mother since she was admitted to the ICU and has been discharged from the hospital for so many days. Even though the two communities are only a few hundred meters away, we are still keeping each other isolated.

Before my mother was discharged from the hospital, I contacted the community, property, contact the Hongshan District CDC, professional disinfection of the home, after my mother came back, I asked the errand boy, sent home a lot of fruits and vegetables.

After my mother came back from the hospital, her lungs still have some damage, it is easier to chest short of breath, after all, people lay for so long, a bit weak in all aspects. After a day or two, my father was released from the Golden Pond.

After discharge from the hospital, I specifically told them to sleep in separate rooms, eat separately, do not go out, or continue to separate from each other for a period of time observation. The doctor also gave them some medicine, and now the two of them are home cooking and taking care of themselves.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Mom's hand was used as a publicity shot

Now that I think about it, I think it's relying on my own willpower. In fact, there is no special protection for such a long time, is to take Oseltamivir, one pill a day, close contacts to take 10 days, and some other proprietary Chinese medicine. And then I was cheering up with my girlfriends online, and I wrote a short guide on how to take medicine, what to wash your hands with, what to disinfect, what to eat, how to build up your resistance, and some of the tips I protect myself from, share it with them.

My mother was in hospital for more than 10 days, I did not have time to give themselves to store supplies, cooking, are around the friends, every other time to my door to throw some cooked food, fruit, medicine. On New Year's Eve, I remember that one gave me some fruit, that one gave me some vegetables, and the other one gave me some meat and cooked some frozen dumplings. The whole New Year is me at home alone, no time to eat and drink, a free time on the information about this disease.

In the middle of the care that I have a few days of symptoms, a little stuffy nose, a little sore throat, I quickly take medicine, I thought I must not be infected by the virus, I must hold on. Now that I've been isolated at home for almost 14 days, I'm fortunate to be in good health.

I think the biggest reason for my mom's recovery, besides being physically fit, is that she's a very optimistic person, and we're lucky to have a good attitude about everything. And there are many doctors, nurses to help us, I especially thank them!

After mom got out of the hospital, I had some kind of stress reaction

After 20 days of death and death, I'm afraid to think about it. At its worst, I have nightmares all night long, and sometimes I dream that I'm sick, too, but when I wake up in the morning, I insist on saying to myself, it's okay, i'm sure it's nothing.

Later I talked to a psychologist, she said that the current stress response takes time and self-regulation, to slowly recover. Because my mother was out of the hospital, as if suddenly pulled me from a state inside the real life, or especially nervous spirit. So I didn't get in touch with a lot of people until I was feeling better and I wanted to share my experience with more people.

I think it's a cat-and-mouse disease, and if you're resistant, it can't get in. We Wuhan people have a word, called "do not believe in evil" , I think this is the spirit of our people in Wuhan. You have to have faith, and you have to beat it, beat it, beat it, with the strongest conviction.
